Andy Murray booked his place in the third round of the Shanghai Masters with a straight-sets victory against Jerzy Janowicz on Wednesday.

Murray came through a tight first set before easing across the finish line as he beat his Polish opponent 7-5, 6-2 in one hour and 28 minutes.

It earns more crucial points for Murray in his bid to qualify for the ATP World Tour Finals in London as he prepares to face David Ferrer in the last 16 on Thursday.

