Ferrer is also fighting for a place in London and the Spanird rallied from a set down to beat Martin Klizan 4-6, 7-6(4), 6-4.

There were surprise defeats for both Kei Nishikori and Stan Wawrinka in their opening matches in Shanghai. 

Wawrinka squandered a 3-0 lead in the final set before falling to Gilles Simon 5-7, 7-5, 6-4, while Nishikori, who won two straight titles in Kuala Lumpur and Tokyo, was beaten by Jack Sock 7-6 (5), 6-4. 

